Template class for short numerical vectors, a partial case of

This template class represents short numerical vectors (of 1, 2, 3, 4 ... elements) on which you can perform basic arithmetical operations, access individual elements using [] operator etc. The vectors are allocated on stack, as opposite to std::valarray, std::vector,
etc., which elements are dynamically allocated in the heap.
In addition to the universal notation like
, you can use shorter aliases for the most popular specialized variants of
. Use operator[] to access the elements of
All the expected vector operations are also implemented:
v1 += v2 and other augmenting operations
